# ERP project structure rules

## Architecture layers (strict order)

1. **UI** — `src/app/(app)/**/page.tsx` — layout, tables, dialogs only; no direct Supabase
2. **Client data** — `src/lib/data/<module>.ts` — fetch wrappers, mock fallback
3. **API** — `src/app/api/<module>/route.ts` — auth, validation, call server
4. **Server** — `src/lib/server/<module>.ts` — database, business rules, mappers
5. **Schema** — `supabase/migrations/` — additive, numbered SQL files

Never skip layers. Never call `createAdminClient` from React components.

## Module layout

Each business module (sales, procurement, inventory) uses:

- One server file: `src/lib/server/<module>.ts`
- One API route: `src/app/api/<module>/route.ts` with `resource` query/body param
- Pages under `src/app/(app)/<module>/<entity>/page.tsx`
- Shared UI: `src/components/<module>/` and `src/components/modules/<module>-shared.tsx`
- Types in `src/lib/types/index.ts` (or `types/<module>.ts` if file grows >300 lines)

## Naming

- Tables: `snake_case`, plural (`purchase_orders`, `material_receipt_notes`)
- API resources: `snake_case` plural (`material_requests`, `purchase_orders`)
- React components: `PascalCase`
- Server functions: `verbNoun` (`createPurchaseOrder`, `mapSupplier`)

## Migrations

- Sequential prefix: `0010_`, `0011_`, …
- Idempotent where possible (`IF NOT EXISTS`, `DROP POLICY IF EXISTS`)
- One concern per file; document in `PROGRESS_INDEX.md` §8

## Permissions & flags

- Sidebar: role permissions + feature flags (`mod_procurement`, etc.)
- Super Admin (`role-super`): full nav, no flag restrictions
- Per-user grants: `user_module_permissions` table only for **extra** modules

## What not to do

- No new mock-only pages when DB path exists — wire API or mark `coming-soon` in nav
- No duplicate calculation logic — reuse `src/lib/sales/calculations.ts` for line totals until extracted to `lib/documents/calculations.ts`
- No god files >500 lines without splitting
- No committing `.env.local` or secrets
- Update `PROGRESS_INDEX.md` after each module milestone (§2, §7, §8)

## Session start checklist

1. Read `PROGRESS_INDEX.md`
2. Read `docs/EXTRA_FEATURES.md` if adding user-requested behavior
3. Read module doc if exists (`docs/PROCUREMENT_FLOW.md`)
4. Match patterns from the nearest completed module (Sales)

## Cursor rules (always apply)

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `erp-project-structure.mdc` | Layers, naming, migrations |
| `erp-docs-and-features.mdc` | Sync PROGRESS_INDEX + build docs on every feature |
| `erp-code-quality.mdc` | Quality bar, flags, tsc, no god files |
